<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>My New Hugo Site</title><link>https://felipefarias.xyz/tags/arch/</link><description>Recent content in arch on My New Hugo Site</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2022 23:51:06 -0400</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://felipefarias.xyz/tags/arch/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Arch SURF Browser</title><link>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-surf/</link><pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2022 23:51:06 -0400</pubDate><guid>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-surf/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://felipefarias.xyz/guides">Go Back&amp;hellip;&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 id="clone-surf">Clone Surf&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ git clone https://git.suckless.org/surf
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="install-the-following-dependencies">Install the following dependencies.&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacman -S webkit2gtk gcr
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="compile-surf">Compile Surf&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ sudo make clean install
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="extra-packages-for-surf">Extra packages for surf&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>By default surf cant play youtube videos.
Your system will need the following packaged for it to work.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacman -S gstreamer gst-plugins-good gst-libav gst-plugins-base xdg-utils
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div></description></item><item><title>Arch Dwm Dmenu</title><link>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-dwm-dmenu/</link><pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2022 23:50:53 -0400</pubDate><guid>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-dwm-dmenu/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://felipefarias.xyz/guides">Go Back&amp;hellip;&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 id="dwm--dmenu">dwm &amp;amp; dmenu&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Install the following dependencies&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacman -S xorg-server xorg-xini libxinerama libxft webkit2gtk
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="clone-dwm--dmenu">Clone dwm &amp;amp; dmenu&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ git clone https://git.suckless.org/dwm
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ git clone https://git.suckless.org/dmenu
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="compile-the-cloned-repos-with">Compile the cloned repos with&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ doas make clean install -C /path/to/dwm
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ doas make clean install -C /path/to/dmenu
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="create-a-x-config-file">Create a X config file&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;exec dwm&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &amp;gt; ~/.xinitrc
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div></description></item><item><title>Arch Audio Bluetooth</title><link>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-audio-bluetooth/</link><pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2022 23:50:46 -0400</pubDate><guid>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-audio-bluetooth/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://felipefarias.xyz/guides">Go Back&amp;hellip;&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 id="audio">Audio&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacman -S pulseaudio pulsemixer
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>There some time that pulseaudio does not work out of the box. To fix this isue, we need to start it with the following command:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pulseaudio &amp;amp;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="bluetooth">Bluetooth&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacman -S bluez bluez-utils pulseaudio-bluetooth
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Start/Enable Bluetooth Services:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ doas systemctl start bluetooth
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="connecting-and-pairing">Connecting and Pairing&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Use the Bluetooth CLI:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ bluetoothctl
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Now run the following to setup bluetooth.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>bluetooth&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># power on&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>bluetooth&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># agent on&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>bluetooth&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># default-agent&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>The next step is scanning near devices and pairing to them.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In my case I have a HUAWEI FreeBuds and we will use the _ MAC Adress _ to pair and connect to them.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>bluetooth&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># scan on&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>NEW&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span> Device 2C:C5:46:5F:B8:29 HUAWEI FreeBuds Pro
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>bluetooth&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># pair 2C:C5:46:5F:B8:29&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>bluetooth&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># connect 2C:C5:46:5F:B8:29&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Finally, if you want to automatically connect to this device in the future:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>bluetooth&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># trust 2C:C5:46:5F:B8:29&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="power-on-on-system-startup">&amp;ldquo;Power on&amp;rdquo; on System startup&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Bluetooth is not powered on startup or after resume.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>To enable this go to /etc/bluetooth/main.conf , uncomment and set to true the following:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>Policy&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>AutoEnable&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>true
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div></description></item><item><title>Arch BIOS Install</title><link>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-bios-install/</link><pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2022 23:50:34 -0400</pubDate><guid>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-bios-install/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://felipefarias.xyz/guides">Go Back&amp;hellip;&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Should be connected to the internet via cable, for wifi refer to the arch wiki.&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 id="sync-time-protocol">Sync time protocol&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ timedatectl set-ntp true
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="partitions-get-disks">Partitions Get disks&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ lsblk
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="enter-your-hardware-storage">Enter your hardware storage&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ fdisk /dev/sdx
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="partition-the-disks-as-you-like">Partition the disks as you like.&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>For this tutorial i will be doing 2 partitions&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>SWAP partition with 10GB
Storage partition with remaining space. (Remember to put the BOOT flag with &amp;lsquo;a&amp;rsquo; in fdisk)&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;h1 id="format-the-partitions">Format the partitions&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>This is the storage partition&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdx
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="format-swap-partition">Format SWAP partition.&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mkswap /dev/sdxN
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="mount-of-partitions">Mount of partitions&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Storage partition&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mount /dev/sdxN /mnt
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Mount SWAP partition&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ swapon /dev/sdx
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="installing-base-system">Installing base system&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacstrap /mnt base base-devel linux-lts linux-firmware vim git networkmanager
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="generate-fstab">Generate FSTAB&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ genfstab -U /mnt &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /mnt/etc/fstab
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="change-installation-medium">Change installation medium&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ arch-chroot /mnt
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="enable-networkmanager">Enable NetworkManager&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ systemctl enable NetworkManager
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="timezone">Timezone&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ ln -sf /usr/share/zoneinfo/Chile/Continental /etc/localtime
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ hwclock --systohc
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="change-localegen">Change locale.gen&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Edit the /etc/locale.gen file and uncomment your language, in my case is
en_US-UTF-8 UTF-8
Enter the following command:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ locale-gen
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="edit-localeconf">Edit locale.conf&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;LANG=en_US.UTF-8&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /etc/locale.conf
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="add-hostname">Add hostname&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>$ echo &amp;ldquo;yourHostName&amp;rdquo; &amp;gt; /etc/hostname&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 id="add-hosts">Add hosts&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Edit /etc/hosts:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>127.0.0.1 localhost
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>::1 localhost
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="add-a-password-to-your-root">Add a password to your root&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ passwd
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="set-the-bootloader">Set the bootloader&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Download following software&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacman -S grub
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="grub-install">GRUB install&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Do this to the whole device where Arch is installed&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ grub-install /dev/sdx
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mkinitcpio -P
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="add-new-user">Add new user&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ useradd -mG wheel newUser
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ passwd newUser
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>RESTART YOUR SYSTEM AND YOU ARE READY TO GO.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Arch UEFI Install</title><link>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-uefi-install/</link><pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2022 23:50:28 -0400</pubDate><guid>https://felipefarias.xyz/guides/arch-uefi-install/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://felipefarias.xyz/guides">Go Back&amp;hellip;&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Should be connected to the internet via cable, for wifi refer to the arch wiki.&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 id="sync-time-protocol">Sync time protocol&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ timedatectl set-ntp true
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="partitions-get-disks">Partitions Get disks&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ lsblk
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="enter-your-hardware-storage">Enter your hardware storage&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ fdisk /dev/sdx
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>For this tutorial I will be doing 2 partitions.&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>200MB UEFI partition&lt;/li>
&lt;li>EFI System (press t and then 1 for EFI) Full storage&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Remaining size.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h1 id="format-partitions-efi-partition">Format partitions EFI Partition&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mkfs.fat -F32 /dev/sdx
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdx
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="mount-of-partitions">Mount of partitions&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Storage partition&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mount /dev/sdx /mnt
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="efi-partition">EFI partition&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mkdir /mnt/boot/
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mount /dev/sdx /mnt/boot
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="installing-base-system">Installing base system&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacstrap /mnt base base-devel linux-lts linux-firmware vim git
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>For WiFi Internet add:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>dhpcd iwd
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>For Wired Internet add:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>networkmanager
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="generate-fstab">Generate FSTAB&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ genfstab -U /mnt &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /mnt/etc/fstab
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="change-installation-medium">Change installation medium&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ arch-chroot /mnt
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="create-swap-file">Create SWAP file.&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ fallocate -l 2GB /swapfile
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ chmod &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">600&lt;/span> /swapfile
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ mkswap /swapfile
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ swapon /swapfile
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="add-swapfile-to-fstab">Add SWAPFILE to FSTAB&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;/swapfile none swap defaults 0 0&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /etc/fstab
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="timezone">Timezone&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ ln -sf /usr/share/zoneinfo/Chile/Continental /etc/localtime
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ hwclock --systohc
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="change-etclocalegen">Change /etc/locale.gen&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Use a text editor to edit this file and search for your use case.
This is used to use your local standards (More info &lt;a href="https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Locale">here&lt;/a>)&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In my case, I&amp;rsquo;ll use a shortcut.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;en_US.UTF-8 UTF-8&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /etc/locale.gen
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="generate-the-locale">Generate the locale&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ locale-gen
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="edit-localeconf">Edit locale.conf&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ vim /etc/locale.conf
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="add-hostname">Add hostname&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;yourHostName&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /etc/hostname
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="edit-etchosts">Edit /etc/hosts&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>127.0.0.1 localhost
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>::1 localhost
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="secure-your-root-user">Secure your root user&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ passwd
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="set-grub-boot-loader">Set grub (boot loader)&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e">#Download GRUB and EFIBOOTMGR&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ pacman -S grub efibootmgr
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ grub-install --target&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>x86_64-efi --efi-directory&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>/boot --bootloader-id&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>GRUB
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="add-new-user">Add New User&lt;/h1>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ useradd -mG wheel newUser
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ passwd newUser
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>RESTART YOUR SYSTEM AND YOU ARE READY TO GO.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>